00:06:03.320 --> 00:06:06.640
So in essence, what that means is three things, right?

00:06:06.640 --> 00:06:12.200
One is we don't, we make sure that everything that we build as a business, not just the

00:06:12.200 --> 00:06:15.679
product team or the ops team or whichever team, everything we've built as a business

00:06:15.679 --> 00:06:18.600
all ladders up to what the business eventually wants to achieve.

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:23.519
So we are the truth seekers that make sure that anything that's being built, we keep

00:06:23.519 --> 00:06:26.559
everybody honest and accountable that these are the right things to build for the business.

00:06:26.559 --> 00:06:30.959
So you can use big words like strategy or vision and stuff like that.

00:06:30.959 --> 00:06:34.200
But at the end of the day for me, it's numbers that all ladder up to what the business needs

00:06:34.200 --> 00:06:35.200
to achieve.

00:06:35.200 --> 00:06:37.160
So we are the truth seekers that help achieve that.

00:06:37.160 --> 00:06:39.660
So that's number one.

00:06:39.660 --> 00:06:45.239
Number two, what that also means is we are the team that keeps people accountable in

00:06:45.239 --> 00:06:48.880
the fact that if we can build something, we can, we can all think it's a great idea,

00:06:48.880 --> 00:06:51.920
but somebody has to run an experiment to figure out if it's the right idea, if it actually

00:06:51.920 --> 00:06:52.920
works.

00:06:52.920 --> 00:06:57.760
The thing with having ideas is anybody can have an idea, but does it actually work and

00:06:57.760 --> 00:07:01.399
measuring it and keeping everyone honest and accountable and in an unbiased manner, that's

00:07:01.399 --> 00:07:02.399
the other thing.

00:07:02.399 --> 00:07:05.559
So apart from truth seeking, we also make sure that we experiment a lot.

00:07:05.559 --> 00:07:09.559
But the third and most important part that we do is the fact that we try to bring teams

00:07:09.559 --> 00:07:10.640
together and connect the dots.

00:07:10.640 --> 00:07:15.880
So the problem with having a much bigger business is everybody's focused on their part of the

00:07:15.880 --> 00:07:16.880
business.

00:07:16.880 --> 00:07:19.040
And this word that gets thrown around with the silo.

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:20.399
So nobody connects the dots.

00:07:20.399 --> 00:07:25.160
I like to think of my role and my team's role as being the people who help connect the dots.

00:07:25.160 --> 00:07:31.200
So my favorite character growing up from Sherlock Holmes was not Sherlock Holmes himself, who

00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:33.040
seemed to always solve the problems.

00:07:33.040 --> 00:07:37.760
For those of you know, Sherlock's brother, Moria, Mycroft Holmes was the person who could

00:07:37.799 --> 00:07:41.559
actually connect all the dots and sit in a room and see everything that's going on and

00:07:41.559 --> 00:07:43.239
understand why something actually happened.

00:07:43.239 --> 00:07:45.959
So being able to know the second and third are the things and connecting dots.

00:07:45.959 --> 00:07:48.000
So those are three things that we do.

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:51.920
And that's what we mean by being true partners is we are very helpful to the business in

00:07:51.920 --> 00:07:54.720
actually making sure what we do is the right thing for us to do.

00:07:54.720 --> 00:07:55.720
That's what we do.

