00:07:58.679 --> 00:08:04.320
So I'm thinking of myself using DoorDash and was wondering if you could give us an example

00:08:04.320 --> 00:08:09.480
of something that your team is impacting across the business or maybe an example use case.

00:08:10.959 --> 00:08:14.440
Sure, I can quite a few things I come to mind.

00:08:14.839 --> 00:08:19.519
One thing I can talk about is, for example, if you see when you shop for something on

00:08:19.519 --> 00:08:25.440
DoorDash, you have a carousel that shows you what you need to see instead of if you let

00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:31.279
people decide what needs to be shown on the carousel, the challenge is there is a very

00:08:31.279 --> 00:08:35.479
delicate balance between completely personalizing it and going the I don't want to name big

00:08:35.479 --> 00:08:39.119
brands that are not ours, going through a music subscription platform route where you

00:08:39.119 --> 00:08:42.880
saw things that slowly become completely irrelevant because it's super personalized.

00:08:42.880 --> 00:08:47.640
I have never seen it before, or you can make it super manual and everybody sets up what

00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:50.760
restaurants you need to see and we need to strike a delicate balance between that.

00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:55.239
So every time you open the app and you see a list of restaurants there or a list of stores

00:08:55.239 --> 00:09:00.919
that you want to shop from, the team has actually thought about a very a solution that can

00:09:01.280 --> 00:09:04.880
solve for both. It can augment both the personalized side of things and also provide the

00:09:04.880 --> 00:09:07.239
operators the right set of inputs and the right set of parameters.

00:09:07.239 --> 00:09:11.760
So we come up with something called the heuristics, which is if you show people X number

00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:15.880
of carousels, Y number of times and X number of restaurants, there are X percent probability

00:09:15.880 --> 00:09:17.520
they cannot. So they know what they need to show.

00:09:17.520 --> 00:09:21.280
And and if they want to push their own restaurants, if account managers want to make

00:09:21.280 --> 00:09:24.799
their restaurant pop up, they know that that doesn't need to show up, whatever.

00:09:24.840 --> 00:09:26.159
There's a number of times that need to show up.

00:09:26.159 --> 00:09:30.159
So we come up with these heuristics and magic numbers that we provide people that can then

00:09:30.159 --> 00:09:33.280
be plugged into the personalized platform as inputs from the operator side.

00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:37.599
So we bridge the gap of being not completely manual, not completely personalized, but a

00:09:37.599 --> 00:09:38.679
good balance, of course.

00:09:38.799 --> 00:09:41.440
That's an example of what you see from the output of the team.

