00:09:58.559 --> 00:10:05.719
I'm wondering if you could talk about some of the the challenges that that you all try to

00:10:05.719 --> 00:10:10.479
deal with that door dash with data and if you could talk about some of the methods that

00:10:10.479 --> 00:10:15.000
maybe you use, like modeling or deep learning or some of those things.

00:10:16.400 --> 00:10:18.000
So, yeah, that's pretty much it.

00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:25.119
Sure. So we the team works on all aspects of the business.

00:10:25.119 --> 00:10:26.559
So we have three parts of the business.

00:10:26.719 --> 00:10:30.239
So we have the consumers, people like you and I who shop on DoorDash, then we have the

00:10:30.239 --> 00:10:33.679
merchants who are the restaurants and the retail partners who sell on DoorDash, and we

00:10:33.679 --> 00:10:35.919
have the Dasher partners who are the people who actually deliver.

00:10:36.159 --> 00:10:41.479
So we tackle and touch lives of all of these individual people in different ways, be it

00:10:41.479 --> 00:10:43.880
what they buy, where they buy from and how they get delivered.

00:10:45.200 --> 00:10:46.919
What kind of things do we try to tackle with data?

00:10:46.919 --> 00:10:53.119
Like I said, in the sum essence of what we try to do is instead of what we realized is a

00:10:53.119 --> 00:10:54.520
blanket approach does not work.

00:10:54.559 --> 00:10:57.880
So if you want to come up with a pricing mechanism, having the same pricing mechanism

00:10:57.880 --> 00:11:03.359
across all countries does not work like that's we all know and we all agree that having a

00:11:03.359 --> 00:11:08.239
one is to an approach makes no sense because having the same pricing for all markets is

00:11:08.239 --> 00:11:11.799
not good. And then somebody can come up with an amazing approach saying maybe we should

00:11:11.799 --> 00:11:13.159
personalize pricing for everybody.

00:11:13.200 --> 00:11:14.840
That's what the end of pricing is.

00:11:15.080 --> 00:11:19.599
And trust me when I say that that also does not work because extreme personalization also

00:11:19.599 --> 00:11:21.559
does not work because it does not work for the edge cases.

00:11:21.559 --> 00:11:27.159
What we need, we've realized at Dodash is a balance for having personalization, but

00:11:27.159 --> 00:11:30.799
also at the same time having the business context built in because when you let

00:11:30.799 --> 00:11:34.239
personalization solve for a problem, the objective function of personalization could be

00:11:34.239 --> 00:11:40.320
say conversion or whatever it is, which basically means that you're not solving for

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:44.119
immediate business needs, which could be getting more new customers or making a

00:11:44.119 --> 00:11:47.280
particular restaurant's work or making some particular markets grow faster.

00:11:47.280 --> 00:11:52.239
So if you want to have multiple optimization features, what do you realize is the better

00:11:52.239 --> 00:11:55.000
team comes in is we try to find the balance between both.

00:11:55.239 --> 00:11:58.640
So like I said, the kind of problems we try to solve is how do you take something that's

00:11:58.640 --> 00:12:03.239
extremely personalized and apply the human element to it by providing the business the

00:12:03.239 --> 00:12:04.880
right levers to tweak.

00:12:04.880 --> 00:12:05.880
So we come up with a lever.

00:12:05.880 --> 00:12:10.039
So to your question, a lot of what we do is we do a lot of experimentation created work,

00:12:10.359 --> 00:12:15.200
which gives us the relationship between an input variable and a set of a lot of input

00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:16.320
variables instead of output variables.

00:12:16.320 --> 00:12:19.960
So if, say, conversion is your output variable, what is the relationship to all the

00:12:19.960 --> 00:12:23.359
input variables? And we do multiple studies, short term, long term and long term

00:12:23.359 --> 00:12:27.520
holdouts to understand if one person improvement in conversion happens, what does it

00:12:27.520 --> 00:12:29.760
mean long term for retention, et cetera, et cetera, et cetera.

00:12:30.080 --> 00:12:33.479
If one extra impression happens here, what does it mean in terms of the merchants

00:12:33.479 --> 00:12:36.239
revenue, et cetera? So we come up with those relationships.

00:12:36.239 --> 00:12:40.520
And that's what at the end of the day we try to do is distill all the findings into

00:12:40.520 --> 00:12:45.119
those so that eventually we can plug it back into our relatively amazing machine

00:12:45.119 --> 00:12:49.880
learning systems that can then go away and give humans human operator the inputs to

00:12:49.880 --> 00:12:52.119
do what they need to do. So that's that's what I think.

00:12:52.320 --> 00:12:55.679
That's why I look at my teams and some output of what we do.

