00:52:07.080 --> 00:52:11.479
I was just wondering, uh, like with so many techniques and so many things going

00:52:11.479 --> 00:52:15.479
on, especially right now with AI and everything, like how do you keep up to

00:52:15.479 --> 00:52:21.439
date with like the latest models, techniques, methods, anything like that?

00:52:22.320 --> 00:52:26.679
So the one thing I take as a true advantage of working with amazing people

00:52:26.679 --> 00:52:29.040
is everyone's trying to push themselves constantly.

00:52:29.040 --> 00:52:33.040
So people take an active interest in one particular topic and then they take it

00:52:33.040 --> 00:52:37.199
upon themselves to either run a forum or bring a topic or work with the academies.

00:52:37.239 --> 00:52:39.439
For example, I can talk about the experimentation topic.

00:52:39.840 --> 00:52:42.320
The extremely obsessive experimentation here.

00:52:42.679 --> 00:52:44.479
And there's only so much you can do with experimentation.

00:52:44.479 --> 00:52:47.360
So after a point, you need to understand how to improve it with

00:52:47.360 --> 00:52:48.800
better variable reduction techniques.

00:52:48.800 --> 00:52:49.719
How can you improve it?

00:52:50.040 --> 00:52:51.040
Better sampling techniques.

00:52:51.239 --> 00:52:55.439
So what the team does is they go away, work with, um, professors from academia

00:52:55.439 --> 00:52:59.239
who also are also searching on the topic, bring them in, help them talk to us

00:52:59.239 --> 00:53:01.800
about a particular area that everyone's solving and talk about.

00:53:01.800 --> 00:53:05.040
So what the team does is they take extreme interest in these topics.

00:53:05.040 --> 00:53:07.199
And so each person has a passion project.

00:53:07.520 --> 00:53:08.280
They work on it.

00:53:08.280 --> 00:53:11.679
So causal inference is a massive thing here because everyone likes

00:53:11.679 --> 00:53:12.719
to know why something happens.

00:53:12.760 --> 00:53:13.760
We all live for that.

00:53:14.120 --> 00:53:17.919
And so there is a group of people who always, every fortnight bring an

00:53:17.919 --> 00:53:21.320
interesting causal inference topic, either themselves or from outside.

00:53:21.320 --> 00:53:22.679
And so you can then subscribe to it.

00:53:22.679 --> 00:53:23.959
And if you're interested in it, you can go.

00:53:24.000 --> 00:53:28.879
So the answer to it is the team takes an active effort and it's all community

00:53:29.320 --> 00:53:32.479
team runs it for their own benefit and others benefit.

